Ne Yapabiliriz? - What Can We Do?

u anda sadece products veri setinde eksik veriler var. Currently, there are missing values only in the products dataset. Bu verileri aadaki ekilde doldurabiliriz: We can handle these missing values like that :

product_weight_g, product_length_cm, product_height_cm, product_width_cm stunlarndaki eksik deerleri ortalama ile doldurabiliriz. We can fill the missing values in product_weight_g, product_length_cm, product_height_cm, and product_width_cm with the mean.

product_name_lenght, product_description_lenght, product_photos_qty stunlarndaki eksik satrlar silebiliriz. We can remove the rows with missing values in product_name_lenght, product_description_lenght, and product_photos_qty.

# Filling missing values with the mean for numeric columns in 'products'
# Saysal stunlar iin eksik deerleri ortalama ile dolduruyoruz
products$product_weight_g[is.na(products$product_weight_g)] <- mean(products$product_weight_g, na.rm = TRUE)
products$product_length_cm[is.na(products$product_length_cm)] <- mean(products$product_length_cm, na.rm = TRUE)
products$product_height_cm[is.na(products$product_height_cm)] <- mean(products$product_height_cm, na.rm = TRUE)
products$product_width_cm[is.na(products$product_width_cm)] <- mean(products$product_width_cm, na.rm = TRUE)

# Dropping rows with missing values for 'product_name_lenght', 'product_description_lenght', and 'product_photos_qty'
# 'product_name_lenght', 'product_description_lenght', ve 'product_photos_qty' stunlarndaki eksik satrlar siliyoruz
products <- products[!is.na(products$product_name_lenght), ]
products <- products[!is.na(products$product_description_lenght), ]
products <- products[!is.na(products$product_photos_qty), ]

# Average payment value by payment type
# deme trne gre ortalama deme deerini hesaplyoruz
average_payment_value <- aggregate(payment_value ~ payment_type, data=order_payments, FUN=mean)

A/B Testi statistiksel Anlamllk - A/B Test Statistical Significance

Ortalama deme deerleri arasndaki farkn istatistiksel olarak anlaml olup olmadn test etmek iin bir t-test yapabiliriz. We can perform a t-test to check if the difference in average payment values is statistically significant.

# Subsetting the payment data for two payment types
# ki deme yntemi iin deme verilerini alt kmelere ayryoruz
payment_type_1 <- subset(order_payments, payment_type == "credit_card")$payment_value
payment_type_2 <- subset(order_payments, payment_type == "boleto")$payment_value

# Performing the t-test
# T-test uyguluyoruz
t_test_result <- t.test(payment_type_1, payment_type_2)

# Displaying the t-test result
# T-test sonucunu grntlyoruz
print(t_test_result)
## 
##  Welch Two Sample t-test
## 
## data:  payment_type_1 and payment_type_2

##  14.91914 21.65003
## sample estimates:
## mean of x mean of y

T-Test Sonularn nceleme - Reviewing T-Test Results

Sonularn Yorumu - Interpretation of Results:

t-deeri (t-value): 10.649

Bu, iki grup arasndaki farkn bykln len bir deerdir. Ne kadar bykse, fark o kadar anlamldr. The t-value of 10.649 indicates the magnitude of the difference between the two groups. The larger the value, the more significant the difference.

p-deeri (p-value): 2.2e-16den kk

Bu, istatistiksel anlamll belirleyen nemli bir deerdir. Eer p-deeri 0.05ten kkse, farkn ans eseri olumad ve istatistiksel olarak anlaml olduu kabul edilir. Burada p-deeri 0.05ten ok daha kk, yani fark istatistiksel olarak anlaml. The p-value is less than 2.2e-16, which is well below 0.05. This means the difference between the two payment methods is statistically significant.

Gven Aral (Confidence Interval): 14.92 ile 21.65

Bu aralk, iki grup arasndaki farkn %95 gvenle bu deerler arasnda olduunu gsterir. The confidence interval between 14.92 and 21.65 indicates that we can be 95% confident that the true difference between the means lies within this range.

Ortalama Deerler (Mean Estimates):

credit_card (x): 163.32 boleto (y): 145.03 credit_card ile yaplan demelerin ortalama deeri boleto ile yaplan demelerden daha yksek. The mean for credit_card payments is 163.32, which is higher than the mean for boleto payments (145.03).

Sonu - Conclusion

Bu t-test sonularna gre, credit_card ve boleto deme yntemleri arasndaki ortalama deme deerleri arasnda istatistiksel olarak anlaml bir fark var. credit_card ile yaplan demeler ortalama olarak daha yksek.

The results of this t-test show that there is a statistically significant difference between the average payment values for credit_card and boleto. Payments made via credit_card are on average higher.

  • cama_mesa_banho (Bedding, table, and bath products) is the top-selling category with a total payment value of 1,712,553.7 BRL.
  • beleza_saude (Gzellik ve salk) kategorisi 1,657,373.1 BRL ile ikinci srada. beleza_saude (Beauty and health) is the second top-selling category with a total of 1,657,373.1 BRL.
  • informatica_acessorios (Bilgisayar aksesuarlar) 1,585,330.4 BRL ile nc srada. informatica_acessorios (Computer accessories) ranks third with 1,585,330.4 BRL.

Popler Kategoriler:Popular Categories

  • Bu liste, hangi rn kategorilerinin mteriler tarafndan en ok tercih edildiini gsterir. This list shows which product categories are most preferred by customers.

  • En ok sat yapan kategoriler, yatak/masa/banyo, gzellik/salk ve bilgisayar aksesuarlar gibi eitli rn gruplarna yayld. The top-selling categories span a variety of product groups such as bedding/table/bath, beauty/health, and computer accessories.

zm - Solution:

  1. order_items ve order_payments Stunlarndaki Tekrar Eden Satrlarn Ynetilmesi - Managing Duplicates in order_items and order_payments Columns:

  • Bu tekrar eden deerler, ayn siparie ait birden fazla e ve deme yntemi olduu iin normaldir. Ancak, her sipariin yalnzca bir sat deeri olmas gerektiinden, tekrar eden satrlar ortalama veya toplam deerler alarak gruplandrabiliriz. These duplicate values are normal because there are multiple items and payment methods for the same order. However, since each order should only have one sales value, we can group duplicate rows by averaging or totaling them.

  • order_items ve order_payments veri setlerindeki tekrar eden siparileri gruplandrarak ilemi devam ettireceiz. We will continue the process by grouping the recurring orders in the order_items and order_payments data sets.

Mteri Eyaletlerine Gre Sat Analizi - Customer State Sales Analysis

}

ARIMA Model Performans Metrii - ARIMA Model Performance Metrics

Modelin doruluunu deerlendirmek iin aadaki hata metrikleri kullanlr. Bu metrikler, modelin tahmin ettii deerler ile gerek deerler arasndaki farklar ler. te her bir metriin anlam: (The following error metrics are used to evaluate the accuracy of the model. These metrics measure the differences between the values predicted by the model and the actual values. Here is what each metric means:)

  1. ME (Mean Error - Ortalama Hata):
    • Tahmin edilen deerlerle gerek deerler arasndaki ortalama sapmadr. Eer 0a yaknsa, model genel olarak dengeli tahmin yapyor demektir.
    • The average difference between the predicted and actual values. If its close to 0, the model is unbiased.
  2. RMSE (Root Mean Squared Error - Kk Ortalama Kare Hatas):
    • Hatalarn karelerinin ortalamasnn karekkdr. Hata miktarn ifade eder; dk bir deer daha iyi bir model performansna iaret eder.
    • The square root of the average of squared errors. A lower value indicates a better model performance.
  3. MAE (Mean Absolute Error - Ortalama Mutlak Hata):
    • Gerek deerlerle tahmin edilen deerler arasndaki mutlak farklarn ortalamasdr. Hata orann verir; dk olmas istenir.
    • The average of absolute differences between actual and predicted values. Lower values indicate better performance.
  4. MPE (Mean Percentage Error - Ortalama Yzde Hatas):
    • Gerek deerlerle tahmin edilen deerler arasndaki yzde farknn ortalamasdr. Negatif ya da pozitif olabilir, modelin sapma ynn gsterir.
    • The average percentage difference between actual and predicted values. Can be positive or negative, indicating model bias direction.
  5. MAPE (Mean Absolute Percentage Error - Ortalama Mutlak Yzde Hatas):
    • Gerek deerlerle tahmin edilen deerler arasndaki mutlak yzde farkdr. Daha dk bir MAPE deeri daha iyi bir model performans anlamna gelir.
    • The average of the absolute percentage differences between actual and predicted values. Lower MAPE indicates better accuracy.
  6. MASE (Mean Absolute Scaled Error - Ortalama Mutlak lekli Hata):
    • Hatalar leklendirir ve karlatrma yapmay salar. 1den kk deerler modelin iyi olduunu gsterir.
    • Scales errors to allow for comparison. Values less than 1 indicate that the model is performing well.
  7. ACF1 (Autocorrelation at Lag 1 - Gecikme 1de Otokorelasyon):
    • Tahmin hatalar arasndaki otokorelasyon derecesini ler. 0a yakn bir deer, model hatalarnn rastgele olduunu gsterir.
    • Measures the autocorrelation of forecast errors at lag 1. Values near 0 indicate that forecast errors are random.

Nasl Yorumlanmal? - How to Interpret?

  • ME deeri 0a yaknsa, model tahminlerinde sistematik bir hata yapmyor demektir. If the ME value is close to 0, the model does not make a systematic error in its predictions.
  • RMSE ve MAE deerleri ne kadar dkse, model o kadar doru tahminler yapyor demektir. The lower the RMSE and MAE values, the more accurate the predictions the model makes.
  • MPE ve MAPE deerleri, modelin tahmin ettii deerlerin ne kadar isabetli olduunu yzdesel olarak gsterir. MPE and MAPE values show how accurate the values predicted by the model are as a percentage.
  • MASE deeri 1den kkse, model gemi ortalamalardan daha iyi tahmin yapyor demektir. If the MASE value is less than 1, the model is making better predictions than historical averages.
  • ACF1 deeri 0a ne kadar yaknsa, modelin hata tahminlerinin rastgele olduunu ve modelin ngr hatalarnn bamsz olduunu gsterir. The closer the ACF1 value is to 0, the more random the models error estimates are and the models prediction errors are independent.

Bu metrikler, modelin tahminlerinin ne kadar gvenilir olduunu ve hangi alanlarda iyiletirme yaplmas gerektiini anlamak iin kullanlr. These metrics are used to understand how reliable the models predictions are and where improvements are needed.

2. RMSE (Kk Ortalama Kare Hatas - Root Mean Squared Error):

  • MAE, tahminlerin ortalama mutlak hatasn gsterir. Model, tahminlerinde ortalama olarak 611.5 birimlik sapma gsteriyor. RMSE ile karlatrldnda, hata dalm kk hatalarla snrl olabilir.

  • MASE deeri 1den ok daha kk, bu da modelin genel olarak baarl olduunu gsteriyor. 1den kk bir MASE deeri, modelin sabit bir ortalamaya dayal tahmine gre daha iyi performans gsterdiini gsterir.
  • A MASE value much smaller than 1 shows that the model is performing well overall. A MASE value less than 1 indicates the model is outperforming a naive forecast based on the mean.

7. ACF1 (Gecikme 1de Otokorelasyon - Autocorrelation at Lag 1):

  • ACF1 deeri neredeyse sfra yakn, bu da modelin tahmin hatalarnn rastgele olduunu ve bir kalba bal olmadn gsterir.
  • The ACF1 value is near zero, indicating that the forecast errors are random and not following a specific pattern.

Genel Yorum - General Interpretation:

The model generally has low error rates. Since MASE is less than 1, some predictions might be accurate. However, the high RMSE, MAE, and especially MPE and MAPE indicate that the model is making significant errors in certain periods and needs performance improvements.

yiletirme nerileri - Improvement Suggestions:

yiletirme almas - Improvment

  • ARIMA modelinin performansn artrmak iin alternatif bir model denemek en etkili stratejilerden biri olabilir. Exponential Smoothing, trend ve mevsimsellik ieren veri setlerinde gl tahminler yapabilme yeteneine sahiptir. Trying an alternative model to improve the performance of the ARIMA model can be one of the most effective strategies. Exponential Smoothing has the ability to make strong predictions in data sets that contain trends and seasonality.
  • Bu yntemle, hem modelin basitliini koruyarak hem de trend ve mevsimsellik bileenlerini yakalayarak daha iyi tahminler yapabiliriz. imdi adm adm Exponential Smoothing modeli oluturalm ve tahmin yapalm. With this method, we can make better predictions by keeping the model simple and capturing the trend and seasonality components.   2. MAE (Ortalama Mutlak Hata):
    • Holt-Winters modelinin MAE deeri (517.0832), ARIMA modelinden daha dk (611.5641). Bu, Holt-Winters modelinin ortalama hata orannn daha dk olduunu ve daha iyi bir tahmin gcne sahip olduunu gsterir.
    • Yorum: Holt-Winters modeli, genel olarak tahmin ettii deerlerin gerek deerlere daha yakn olduunu gsteriyor.
  3. MASE (Ortalama Mutlak lekli Hata):
    • Holt-Winters modelinin MASE deeri (0.1022186), ARIMA modeline gre daha kk (0.1208959). Bu da Holt-Winters modelinin hata orannn leklendirilmi veri zerinde daha iyi olduunu gsteriyor.
    • Yorum: MASE deerlerinin her iki modelde de 1den kk olmas, her iki modelin de makul performans gsterdiini, ancak Holt-Winters modelinin daha stn olduunu gsterir.

Genel Yorum - General Interpretation:

  • Genel sonulara baktmzda, Holt-Winters modeli bu veri seti iin ARIMA modelinden daha iyi performans gstermitir. Hem RMSE hem de MAE asndan daha dk hata oranlarna sahip olduu iin, bu model daha gvenilir ve daha doru tahminler yapyor gibi grnyor. MASE deerlerinin de her iki modelde 1den kk olmas, her iki modelin de makul tahminler yaptn, ancak Holt-Winters modelinin daha tutarl olduunu gsterir.

  • Based on the results, the Holt-Winters model outperforms the ARIMA model for this dataset. With lower RMSE and MAE values, the Holt-Winters model appears to provide more accurate and reliable forecasts. The MASE values being less than 1 for both models indicate that both are reasonable, but the Holt-Winters model shows more consistency and better overall performance.

Modelime Gvenebilir Miyim? - Can I Trust My Model?

  • Evet, Holt-Winters modeline gvenebilirsiniz nk hata oranlar daha dk ve modelin daha doru tahminler yapt gzkyor. Tahminlerinizi bu model zerinden yaparak gelecekteki trendleri analiz edebilirsiniz.

  • Yes, you can trust the Holt-Winters model because it has lower error rates and appears to make more accurate predictions. You can use this model to forecast future trends with more confidence.
